'''George Burleigh''' (1914–1984) was a Canadian swimmer. He won gold at the [[Commonwealth Games]] in 1930 and 1934.<ref>[http://www.gbrathletics.com/commonwealth/swimming.htm COMMONWEALTH GAMES MEDALLISTS - SWIMMING AND DIVING (MEN)] Retrieved 27 March 2017</ref> and held Canadian freestyle swimming records in the 1930s.

==Early life and education==
In 1925, Burleigh began to swim at the [[West End YMCA]] in [[Toronto]].<ref name="mccarty">{{cite magazine |last=McCarty |first=Cressy A.M. |date=July 1945 |title=A Swimming Flashback - George Burleigh |url=https://archive.org/stream/swimnewsn45#page/n5/mode/2up/search/burleigh |magazine=Swim Canada |volume=5 |issue=45 |page=7 |access-date=20 August 2017}}</ref>

==Career==
From 1930 to 1938, Burleigh held every Canadian record in freestyle swimming ranging from the 50 yd freestyle to the mile freestyle.<ref name="mccarty"/> During this time period, he won a total of 7 medals at the [[British Empire Games]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Commonwealth Games Federation - Search Atheletes, Games, Countries, Medals and Games Results |url=http://www.thecgf.com/search/search.asp|website=Commonwealth Games Federation |accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref>

==Retirement==
After ending his swimming career in 1938, Burleigh went to teach at the West End YMCA and retired in [[Wybridge, Ontario]].<ref name="mccarty"/>

==Awards and achievements==
Burleigh was inducted in the [[Canadian Olympic Hall of Fame]] in 1976.<ref>{{cite web |title=Canadian Olympic Hall of Fame|url=http://olympic.ca/canadian-olympic-hall-of-fame/ |website=olympic.ca|accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref> Posthumously, he was inducted in the [[Ontario Aquatic Hall of Fame]] in 2000 <ref>{{cite web|title=Swim - Ontario Hall of Fame|url=http://www.swimontario.com/page.php?id=1648|website=Swim Ontario|accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref> and [[Canada's Sports Hall of Fame]] in 2015.<ref name="sportshall">{{cite web|title=Canada's Sports Hall of Fame |website=sportshall.ca|url=http://www.sportshall.ca/stories.html?proID=556|accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref>

